I was advised to put this book out for January 1st, because “that would be so perfect for those that have resolutions”. However, I didn’t want to release this on January 1st because… well, that would defeat my personal true mission in writing this book. 

So many have asked me how I lost my weight. Sure, the answer is Intermittent Fasting while eating Ketogenic geared meals.  Some of you may know I started on OMAD (one meal a day) and have done that ever since and will continue to do so for the duration of my life; however, there was more to it than that. How did I really make it possible? At first, I have to be honest, I had a hard time putting it into words when doing interviews etc.  So finally decided to put pen to paper and get deep into what really made it possible. 

In this book I speak about not only how I made my health a success, but the mental work I put into handling many of my life’s hurdles.  I wanted to share this simply because it may help someone else as well.  I could go on and on about this topic and would love to one day; for now, I wanted to get this in front of you all so you could really start your work.  This is not for a New Years resolution but for LIFE!

Sending love and Pure Mental Fitness your way! Hugs!

#selflove #mentalhealth  #mentalfitness #purementalfitness #book #author

There are no words to describe where I ended up or even how I got back from that place.  One thing is for sure is I didn’t give up. 

Out of the thousands of pieces of advice I or anyone could give you, I still think the most powerful one is to not give up.  Don’t give up on your goals or yourself.

When I started my journey I didn’t set out to just lose weight I badly wanted to break a cycle.  A cycle of excuses I was making for myself to cope with my circumstances. 

I was making a huge break in my life and wanted so desperately to not go back to where I was.  That was the promise I made to myself…and THAT was the promise I kept! 

Today I live in love, self love and love of the journey ahead.  I never said or thought it would be an easy one.  Yet I lean towards the beautiful parts of what has unfolded before me. 

If you have a life goal, please, hear yourself out, look in the mirror and do it! 
Shout out to @thinkfitnesstoronto @iambishop for the appearance! 🙌👏 Sending love to all of you always!
